# HoundDog ignore file — config-level suppressions for false positives.
# HoundDog 3.1.1 has NO inline source-code suppression syntax — every
# `// hounddog-ignore…`, `// hounddog:ignore`, `// hd-ignore…`,
# `// noqa: hounddog`, etc. variant has been tested and is silently
# ignored by the scanner. See
# .local/skills/security_scan/SKILL.md ("HoundDog suppressions") for
# the full list and rationale. File-glob suppression (this file) is
# the only mechanism that works. Listed defensively for the UUID
# sentinel files too in case future HoundDog rule updates flag them.
#
# Patterns are file globs relative to the repository root, one per
# line. Comments start with `#`.

# Dev-only seed CLI prints the freshly generated seed user's password
# to stdout so operators can copy it. The script is invoked manually
# against a local database; there is no production codepath that runs
# it. See lib/db/src/seed-cli.ts for the inline rationale.
lib/db/src/seed-cli.ts

# UNKNOWN_CLIENT_ID is a deterministic UUIDv5 sentinel used to
